Class MogramException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception

          • sorcer.service.MogramException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ContextException, ExertionException

    public class MogramException
extends ServiceException
    The MogramException represents an exception that is thrown if a mogram is evaluated or performed by a service provider failing to process it correctly. A complementary related throwable and/or ill behaving mogram can be embedded into this exception.
